*****************************Day 17: Install and Configure PostgreSQL***************************

The Nautilus application development team has shared that they are planning to deploy one newly developed application on Nautilus infra in Stratos DC. The application uses PostgreSQL database, so as a pre-requisite we need to set up PostgreSQL database server as per requirements shared below:

PostgreSQL database server is already installed on the Nautilus database server.

a. Create a database user kodekloud_gem and set its password to 8FmzjvFU6S.

b. Create a database kodekloud_db9 and grant full permissions to user kodekloud_gem on this database.

Note: Please do not try to restart PostgreSQL server service.

Ans :

thor@jumphost ~$ ssh peter@stdb01

[peter@stdb01 ~]$ sudo su - 

[root@stdb01 ~]# sudo systemctl status postgresql
vice: Failed to send unit change signal for postgresql.service: Connection reset by peer

[root@stdb01 ~]# systemctl enable postgresql 
Created symlink /etc/systemd/system/multi-user.target.wants/postgresql.service â†’ /usr/lib/systemd/system/postgresql.service.

[root@stdb01 ~]# systemctl start  postgresql 

[root@stdb01 ~]# systemctl status  postgresql 


[root@stdb01 ~]# sudo -i -u postgres

[postgres@stdb01 ~]$ psql
psql (13.14)
Type "help" for help.

postgres=# CREATE USER kodekloud_gem WITH PASSWORD '8FmzjvFU6S';
CREATE ROLE
postgres=# CREATE DATABASE kodekloud_db9;
CREATE DATABASE
postgres=# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE kodekloud_db9 to kodekloud_gem
postgres-# \q
[postgres@stdb01 ~]$ exit
logout


[root@stdb01 ~]# psql  -U kodekloud_gem -d kodekloud_db9 -h localhost -W
Password: 
psql (13.14)
Type "help" for help.

kodekloud_db9=> 


done !!!